Description. Macroscopic features. Approximately hemispherical, with broad gutters between tubercles when relaxed. The sponge constricts upon collection, closing the gutters and placing the tubercles in contact. The width and depth of the gutters varies greatly in field photos, as does color (from yellow to orange, but sometimes covered in a dark red growth of apparent algae). As this species has been well described elsewhere (
Austin et al. 2014
), I focused on improving our understanding of the quantitative aspects of spicules that have been shown to vary among samples.
